d><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a good idea</span><hr size=1> heheh, i must admit, I loved this zone, with both of my rogues.  Great layout, interesting mobs and design, and the maze...woohoo<br>
<br>
as far as your comments on the other non luclin zones...<br>
<br>
Karnors - this zone suck, in my opinion, due to it being the first &quot;high&quot; level zone for many people.  the inexperience causes many trains and problems.  camp stealing, zone training, bad/dumb pulling...i avoided KC my entire career, I hate that zone.<br>
<br>
Howling Stones - key is a problem, and it's a bit out of the way, even with the SFire port<br>
<br>
Kael - ive never noticed the xp here being any good.  giants have so many HPs that you cant kill as fast as many other zones.  I only faction here.<br>
<br>
Skyshrine - never hunted, cant comment<br>
<br>
Icewell Keep - never hunted, cant comment<br>
<br>
Sirens Grotto - i love this zone, great xp, tons of gems and assorted loot, but a bit of a pain to get to, at least many think so<br>
<br>
Dragon Necropolis - again, another zone i love, but rarely hunt.  certainly no pick up groups like sebilis, which is due (in my opinion) almost entirely to it being a pain to get to<br>
<br>
It's the age-old (EQ age anyway) problem of loot and accessibility.  If youre not a solo class, you must group.  If there are no players in a zone, you can't group.  If there is no incentive (read: loot or really easy xp) in a zone, there won't be any players.  Look at fungus grove...I'm so sick of that zone yet half the people I know haven't ventured out of it more than the occasional raid to other Luclin zones.  Why?  Easy xp, near a portal (nexus) and plenty of ppl there always so that LFG tag can actually work for getting a group.  Katta or SSeru on the other hand?  I've spent a LOT of time in Katta.  Over half of that, I'm the only player there.  Why?  Faction issues, distance to/from a portal, and nobody to group with.<br>
<br>
It dismays me sometimes to know that everyone onilne is paying the same money for their gaming experience, yet there are tons of zones they never see.  People tend to be sheepish in nature, with the majority being followers, not leaders or explorers.  I like exploring <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Shienn<br>
