  I would have to agree, the reason why players choose to hunt in a dungeon (not outdoors) are due to a few key factors:<br>
<br>
1. Accessibility: how far the dungeon is from a wiz/druid port.<br>
    ex: Permafrost, Kaeosora, Kedge, DN - these zones have reduced numbers of players due to how far they are from ports.<br>
<br>
2. Risk vs Reward: Does the loot there justify risking my RL time and difficulty of the dungeon.<br>
    ex: Runnyeye, Splitpaw, Unrest, Befallen,- loot here sucks<br>
<br>
3. &quot;Do-ability&quot;: Is the dungeon easy to &quot;do&quot;? This includes issues such as pathing, types of mobs (ench mobs suck).<br>
   ex: Mistmoore, Splitpaw (ench mobs eveywhere), Hole,      Sirens Grotto - these zones have sucky pathing<br>
<br>
4. Ease of Corpse Recovery: How easy is it to CR your corpse after a wipeout? Many dungeons are underutilized do to the long time it will take for a CR.<br>
   ex: The Hole, DN, SG, Kedge- these take long times to CR<br>
<br>
5. Difficulty of mobs: How difficult is it to kill a mob, how hard they hit, how many ppl it takes to kill one.. etc. <br>
  ex: FG, Velks - These dungeons are highly populated due to the low difficulty of killing the mobs here. Il bet if they upped the difficulty of these mobs, you would see less people.<br>
<br>
These are some of the fundamental reasons why people choose (or choose not) to go to a dungeon zone to group. Maybe if VI had a stable head on their collective shoulders, they would realize these fundamental reasons, and make changes in accordance.<br>
<br>
Najir Treantfyre<br>
60 Warder of Tunare<br>
Lotus Cult<br>
Quellious<br>
